  "prompt": "What are the top 10 most read articles on Wikipedia?",
  "response": "As of my last update in April 2023, the top 10 most read articles on Wikipedia, based on the number of page views, are as follows:\n\n1. **Wikipedia** - The article about Wikipedia itself, providing an overview of the online encyclopedia's history, operation, and features.\n2. **Deaths in 2023** - A regularly updated list of notable deaths in the year 2023.\n3. **ChatGPT** - An article about the AI chatbot developed by OpenAI, which gained significant attention and usage since its release.\n4. **List of highest-grossing films** - An article listing films that have earned the most money at the global box office.\n5. **Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 3** - The Wikipedia page for the Marvel superhero film released in 2023.\n6. **The Last of Us (TV series)** - The article about the HBO adaptation of the popular video game, which premiered in 2023.\n7. **Barbie (film)** - The Wikipedia page for the 2023 film directed by Greta Gerwig, based on the popular Mattel doll.\n8. **Oppenheimer (film)** - The article about the 2023 biographical film directed by Christopher Nolan about physicist J. Robert Oppenheimer.\n9. **J. Robert Oppenheimer** - The Wikipedia page on the theoretical physicist often called the \"father of the atomic bomb.\"\n10. **Taylor Swift** - The article on the American singer-songwriter known for her narrative songwriting and numerous awards.\n\nPlease note that the rankings can change over time due to ongoing events, new releases, and other factors influencing public interest. For the most current information, you should check Wikipedia's own list of most-viewed pages.",
